  "prompt": "Will it be fine if both husband and wife having same blood group?",
  "response": "Yes, it is perfectly fine for both a husband and wife to have the same blood group. The blood group of parents does not directly impact the health or compatibility of their relationship. However, it can influence the blood type of their children and, in rare cases, may be a consideration for certain genetic conditions.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about blood type compatibility or genetic risks, it's best to consult with a healthcare professional or genetic counselor.",
